"Hubert P., Schertzer D., Tchiguirinskai A.I., Bendjoudi H., Lovejoy S., Hallegatte S., Larchevěque M.","A multifractal point of view on climatological evolution [Un point de vue multifractal sur l'évolution climatique]",2002,"Houille Blanche",,"8",,"31","33",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0036462151&partnerID=40&md5=e35d3e0caba1b1a892bdd12f05eed84c","UMR Sisyphe, Ecole des Mines de Paris, 35 rue St Honoré, Fontainebleau 77305, France; LMM, Universite P.and M. Curie, 4 place Jussieu, Paris cedex 05 75252, France; Météo-France, 1 Quai Branly, Paris cedex 05 75252, France; UMR Sisyphe, LGA, Universite P and M Curie, 4 place Jussieu, Paris, cedex 05 75252, France; Physics dept., McGill U., 3600 University St., Montreal, Que. H3A 2T8, Canada; Ecole Natl. de la Meteorologie, Avenue Coriolis, Toulouse 31057, France","Hubert, P., UMR Sisyphe, Ecole des Mines de Paris, 35 rue St Honoré, Fontainebleau 77305, France; Schertzer, D., LMM, Universite P.and M. Curie, 4 place Jussieu, Paris cedex 05 75252, France, Météo-France, 1 Quai Branly, Paris cedex 05 75252, France; Tchiguirinskai, A.I., UMR Sisyphe, LGA, Universite P and M Curie, 4 place Jussieu, Paris, cedex 05 75252, France; Bendjoudi, H., UMR Sisyphe, LGA, Universite P and M Curie, 4 place Jussieu, Paris, cedex 05 75252, France; Lovejoy, S., Physics dept., McGill U., 3600 University St., Montreal, Que. H3A 2T8, Canada; Hallegatte, S., Ecole Natl. de la Meteorologie, Avenue Coriolis, Toulouse 31057, France; Larchevěque, M., LMM, Universite P.and M. Curie, 4 place Jussieu, Paris cedex 05 75252, France","The global warning assumption has not yet been convincingly substantiated from hydrometeorological data analysis. In fact, as the atmosphere and the hydrosphere are highly non linear systems, one cannot expect a linear response to an increase of green house gas concentration because there exists various interactions and feedbacks at different scales between these systems and between their components. Before any prognosis about climate change it is rather indispensable to have a better knowledge of its natural variability. In any case, it will be extremely difficult or even fallacious to separate the anthropogenic and natural variability as it is likely that they strongly interact. To overcome such difficulties we argue that one has to keep as close as possible to the non linear physics of the involved phenomena. This is the objective of a multifractal analysis, which is both multiscale and multiintensity, of the available data.",,"climate change; data processing; fractal analysis; global warming; hydrometeorology; nonlinearity",,,,,,"Bendjoudi, H., Hubert, P., A propos de la distribution statistique des cumuls pluviométriques annuels. Faut-il en finir avec la normalite? (1998) Revue des Sciences de l'Eau, 11 (4), pp. 617-630; Berger, P., (1984) Milankovitch and Climate, (PART 1-2). , (Eds.) Reidel, Boston, 455 p; Hallegatte, S., (2001) Rapport de recherche, , Ecole Nationale de la Météorologie, Toulouse; Hallegatte, S., Biaou, A., Tchiguirin Sakaia, I., Schertzer, D., Hubert, P., Veysseire, J.M., Lovejoy, S., (2002) Law of Rain Rate Extremes, , en préparation; Hubert, P., Tessier, Y., Lovejoy, S., Schertzer, D., Schmitt, F., Ladoy, P., Carbonnel, J.P., Desurosne, I., Multifractals and extreme rainfall events (1993) Geophysical Research Letters, 20, pp. 931-934; Hubert, P., Bendjoudi, H., Schertzer, D., Lovejoy, S., Multifractal taming of extreme hydrometeorological events (2002) The Extremes of the Extremes, 271, pp. 51-56. , July 17-20, 2000, Reykjavik (Iceland), IAHS publication; Johnsen, S.J., Irregular glacial interstadials recorded in a new Greenland ice core (1992) Nature, 359, pp. 311-313; Ladoy, P., Schertzer, D., Lovejoy, S., Une étude d'invariance locale-régionale des températures (1986) La Météorologie, 7, pp. 23-34; Ladoy, P., Lovejoy, S., Schertzer, D., Extreme variability of climatological data : Scaling and intermittency (1991) Non-Linear Variabi